<subSubSection id="FF9D65303419FF9DFF5CC473185293BF" pageId="2" pageNumber="271" type="description">
<paragraph id="B73836BB3419FF9DFF5CC473185293BF" blockId="2.[178,1085,321,431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="271">
C o m m e n t: The previously known distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="70874D383419FF9DFD08C47319419347" authorityName="EPPELSHEIM" authorityYear="1889" box="[742,873,321,343]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93419FF9DFD08C47319419347" box="[742,873,321,343]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="271">A. caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was confined to the Caucasus region (
<collectingCountry id="CF90762B3419FF9DFE96C46C1B979364" box="[376,447,350,372]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="271">Russia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="CF90762B3419FF9DFE3CC46C18009364" box="[466,552,350,372]" name="Georgia" pageId="2" pageNumber="271">Georgia</collectingCountry>
). The only previous Turkish record from 
<collectingRegion id="7543F8593419FF9DFBE7C46C1E159364" box="[1033,1085,350,372]" country="Turkey" name="Ordu" pageId="2" pageNumber="271">Ordu</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D3164B4A3419FF9DFF57C44E1B789382" author="ASSING V" box="[185,336,380,402]" pageId="2" pageNumber="271" pagination="117 - 172" refId="ref5844" refString="ASSING V. (2009 b): On the Staphylinidae of Turkey. VI. Thirteen new species and additional records (Coleoptera). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 79: 117 - 172." type="journal article" year="2009">ASSING 2009b</bibRefCitation>
) refers to 
<taxonomicName id="70874D383419FF9DFE50C44E18CB9381" authority="ASSING, 2009" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2009" box="[446,739,380,401]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Aleochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claviculata">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA93419FF9DFE50C44E18659381" box="[446,589,380,401]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="271">A. claviculata</emphasis>
ASSING, 2009
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D3164B4A3419FF9DFD1CC44E19AD9382" author="ASSING V" box="[754,901,380,402]" pageId="2" pageNumber="271" pagination="355 - 422" refId="ref5879" refString="ASSING V. (2009 c): A revision of Ceranota STEPHENS, subgenus of Aleochara GRAVENHORST (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 59 (2): 355 - 422." type="journal article" year="2009">Assing 2009c</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, the above male represents the first record from 
<collectingCountry id="CF90762B3419FF9DFDC7C4AB185E93BF" box="[553,630,409,431]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="271">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
